## How to Work In This Repo (Agent Rules)

**This project follows the Compass Framework.** The full agent rule set lives in [`framework-rules/RULES.md`](framework-rules/RULES.md). Read it before making any non-trivial change.

The rules in summary — these are **non-negotiable**:

1. **No `if (tenant.id == ...)` or `when (tenant.id)` outside `:app/di/TenantResolverModule.kt`.** Use `TenantFlags` / `TenantParams` for values, polymorphic `@TenantKey`-bound policies for behavior.
2. **`:features` is Logic-Blind.** ViewModels depend on `:core` interfaces only. Onboarding a new tenant must require zero `:features` edits.
3. **`:aos-sdk` is banking-agnostic.** No domain terms (no `Account`, `Money`, `Loan`, `Transfer`, no tenant id) inside the SDK.
4. **One Retrofit family in `:data`** (`Fintech*Api`, split per feature area). No per-tenant Retrofit interface, no per-tenant DTO.
5. **Tenant modules are policies + DI only.** No UI, no networking. Tenant-locked features with their own API/screens go in `:features-{name}` sibling modules.
6. **`:design-system` is tenant-agnostic and domain-agnostic.** Theme + primitive Composables only. Strings live in `strings.xml`.
7. **The tenant binds once at login.** No live tenant swap. Tenant change = logout + login.
8. **Only `BuildConfig.MG_URL` and `BuildConfig.STALE_CONFIG_TTL_MS` are hardcoded.** Everything else comes from `RuntimeConfig` via MG.
9. **Onboarding a new tenant is strictly additive.** New module + one `settings.gradle.kts` include + one `TenantCatalogue` entry. If a tenant-onboarding diff touches `:aos-sdk`, `:core`, `:data`, `:design-system`, `:features`, sibling tenants, or other region bases — push back.
10. **No `variant` terminology.** The variant axis was collapsed into the tenant axis. Use `tenant`, `region`, `TenantContext`, `:tenants:{region}:{tenantSlug}` instead.

For the full taxonomy of legal/illegal patterns, see [`framework-rules/RULES.md`](framework-rules/RULES.md) sections 3–7 and 10.

